


+Tokens Log+

++Description++

The Tokens Log application tracks the usage of authentication tokens across the system.
These tokens are typically used in API calls, automated scripts, or temporary login sessions.
This module allows administrators to monitor access to the system and detect potential misuse or unauthorized attempts.

++List view++

[Insert screenshot of the list view here]

The following fields are displayed in the list view:

- Datetime: When the token was used.
- User: The user associated with the token.
- Token ID: Identifier or fingerprint of the token.
- Action: Operation performed using the token (e.g., login, request).
- IP Address: Origin of the access attempt.


++View entry++

This view displays all information related to a specific token access.

[Insert screenshot of the view entry here]

It includes:

- Datetime: Timestamp of token usage.
- User: Owner of the token.
- Token: Full token or masked fingerprint.
- Action: Description of what the token was used for.
- IP Address: Source IP from which the token was used.
- User-Agent: Browser or client string (if available).
- App/Endpoint: Optional context of the API or function accessed.


